column5: Looks pretty much pre-unibody MacBook Pro to me, by the overall shape and the way the keyboard looks to me. Not sure which OS it currently runs though.

Pretty much how I feel lately; I'm told that comparing myself to others, especially when I'm not doing so well overall, is...not good for me emotionally.  


aand it kind of shows, but man I can't help myself from not doing so. Its true that it seems like I'm putting myself down everytime I do compare how I'm doing against(with?) my peers, but who else can I look up to? Ask them for advice? Yeah, if only I'm so great at communicating, I might.
